Carassed by the touch of fire<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/01 7:46:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wyverns of CS strats..</span><hr size=1> Two-three people quad-kiting in Cobalt will clean out the wyverns in no time. That's the main complaint.<br>
<br>
I started quadding them at 52 with Pillar of Frost, and found that I just about had enough mana to do the job, and if there were too many resists, there could be trouble. However, if you get enough disatnce while they are BoF'd, they will warp back to their spawn; then you can med up a bit, and finish them off with a draught or two - just remember where you pulled from, and hope no one else steals them in the meanwhile (they also forget they are mad at you when they warp, you will not get xp if they are pulled and killed by someone else).<br>
<br>
It is best to pull to the beach. Up top, there is always a chance a drake will jump in, and they are very bad news once they start casting. I generally con a few to find blues (they start getting green at 52), then run by hitting them with Flux staff to pull. With lev up (it hurts otherwise <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), pull off the cliff to the beach, and run around a rock or something to group them up. Be careful first time, let them get close enough that you don't run headlong into them on your first turn. Then run along the edge of the cliff to get some distance, and BoF (or Atols) them all in one shot. I don't recommend BoF on singles to pull, you might run out of mana. Then just PoF (or PoL if you are as high as 54, probably the last level they will be worth it) as usual, running between for proper distance. I like to turn around before nuking, to make sure I don't catch an otter as tehy are running by - you do NOT want an otter camp on you.<br>
<br>
That's about it - it was rare with PoF that all would die at once, generally one or two would resist for half damage or less in the course of the hunt. I have never had PoL resisted at all.<br>
<br>
All that said, out of courtesy, I dont quad kite if there are a bunch of people hunting in the zone. Single pulls are not really that much slower xp gain - since quadding takes a full bar of mana or more, and singles only take a half or less, there is much less down-time with singles, esecially if you get a lot of resists quadding.<br>
<br>
Wyverns are not social, they won't help each other out as long as you stay far enough to not aggro the ones you aren't killing. Drakes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> are</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and will jump in if they get close enough to a wyvern you are killing. The only wyvern that is an exception is Yvolcarn, who is not only social, but often level 51 or higher, and will summon. He also gives a faction hit against CoV and Yelinak, which the unamed ones do not. Stay clear of the part of the beach near the tower - bulthar are very aggro, to everyone, and will kill you fast. Near the very tip of the peninsula are sirens, who you also want to avoid, unless you enjoy being charmed and ganged up on. <p><b>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udamarkifrit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damark Ifrit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/01 8:21:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wyverns of CS strats..</span><hr size=1> I am not sure what I am talking about, othmirs or otter, but I know one of these guy hate drake so much. There r 3 drares there, and only the one flying on route EW from dragon circle up half way to ss portal has a strong effect on the kiting strat. at 54, I usually solo that guy, then start quading. Its not so bad solo that drake, since his nuke is breath waepon = PBAE, so I try not to get too close to him, I use flux staff to judge distance, and Draught for fast nukes. as a matter of fact, he is nice exp, occassional drop spells, gems, etc....<br>
Also, those otter, othmirs whatever down the beach hate drake and wyverns, so u can just lev, and train the drake to their camp. I figure the drake wouldnt respawn until after 2-3 quad kites ( plus med time ).  <p><center>
